    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-11-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="313"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d313">
                <head>313. Letter From the Deputy Under Secretary of State for Political Affairs
                        <persName corresp="#p_JRH1" type="from">Johnson</persName>) to the Deputy
                    Secretary of Defense (<persName corresp="#p_GRL1" type="to"
                        >Gilpatric</persName>)<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d313fn1">Source:
                        Washington National Records Center, RG 330, OSD Files: FRC 66 A 3542,
                        Vietnam 1962, 370.64. Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1962-11-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 9, 1962</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Ros</hi>: I have seen a copy of the proposed
                    memorandum from Secretary <persName corresp="#p_MNRS1">McNamara</persName> to
                    the President which recommends that henceforth defoliation operations in
                    Viet-Nam be conducted under the supervision of the Ambassador and General
                        <persName corresp="#p_HGPD1">Harkins</persName>.<note n="2" xml:id="d313fn2"
                        >The proposed memorandum has not been found; for text as sent to the
                        President on November 16, see <ref target="#d317">Document 317</ref>.</note>
                    I am agreeable to your indicating Department of State concurrence to the
                    memorandum.</p>
                <p>However, I suggest that we ask for regular reporting from Saigon on the
                    effectiveness of the operation as weighed against the harm being done to United
                    States interests by Communist propaganda on the subject.</p>
                <p>If the President approves the memorandum, I suggest Saigon be informed by a joint
                    State-Defense message.</p>
                <p>Sincerely,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Alex</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
